1.title: Dokidoki Dôbutsu Rando
1.plot: Yamato Kazakiri, a young zoologist, comes across a mysterious cube in the woods that transports him to a place inhabited by animal-headed humanoids known as the Zyumans.

2.title: Kono Hoshi o Nameru na yo
2.plot: The Zyumans, stuck in the human world, stay with Yamato's uncle, but Tusk still does not trust Yamato to be the fifth Zyuohger.

3.title: Kaeritaikedo Kaerenai
3.plot: The Zyumans cannot return to Zyuland until they find the missing sixth Champion's Proof.

4.title: Ringu ni Hoero
4.plot: Sela and Leo are kidnapped by the Deathgalien Player Amigarudo to be in his "Battle Show" where two people enter, and only one can leave, and he chooses best friends because it entertains him.

5.title: Jyanguru no Ôjya
5.plot: While chasing down the Deathgalien Player Gaburio, Yamato and the others find a gorilla Zyuman named Larry who has been studying humans for several years. Elsewhere, Azarudo lands on Earth to make Gaburio more powerful.

6.title: Wairudo na Puresento
6.plot: With Yamato using Larry's Zyuman power, Larry begins to age rapidly, threatening his life.

7.title: Gogogo Gôsuto ga Deta
7.plot: Kubaru appears and transforms Amu into one of his servants. To face this unexpected crisis, the Zyuohgers receive some unexpected help from Kamen Rider Ghost.

8.title: Sabanna no Merodî
8.plot: The Deathgalien Player Yabiker attacks with the maddening sound horn of his horn, posing as a challenge to the Zyuohgers, while Leo befriends a young musician after hearing one of his songs.

9.title: Owaranai Ichinichi
9.plot: The Zyuohgers keep defeating the same enemy again and again, unaware that they are under the effect of the sleeping pollen of the Deathgalien Player Hanayaida.

10.title: Mottmo Kiken na Gêmu
10.plot: Ginis, the leader of the Deathgaliens, envelops a large portion of the city into a barrier that disintegrates everything it touches, and the Zyuohgers run against time to find the switch that turns it down as it shrinks little by little, threatening everyone trapped inside, including themselves.

11.title: Doubutsu Daishûgô
11.plot: Despite escaping from the barrier, the Zyuohgers are easily defeated by Gift, the all-powerful destruction machine designed by Ginis. As Gift recharges to resume its attack, Sela and the other Zyumans confront the same "Bird Man" who once rescued Yamato and discover that the sixth Champion's Proof is in his possession. But when they realize that Yamato's true intentions were to send them home and confront Gift alone, the other Zyuohgers decide to return and help him instead, combining all their Zyuoh Cubes into a new, mighty robot.

12.title: Hana no Mijikai Zô
12.plot: After having a disastrous encounter with Genkuro Oiwa, a bookshop owner, Tusk is obliged to work for him during his recovery, while the other Zyuohgers are busy facing the Deathgalien Player Hattena who appears with a plan to destroy the culture of the Earth.

13.title: Sancho no Moku Geisha
13.plot: The Zyuohgers climb Mount Onoiwa along Yuri Igarashi, a young hiker who claims that she had seen the Bird Man they are looking for there.

14.title: Usotsuki Dorobô o Baka-kei
14.plot: Amu befriends Kazuhiro Fuwa and his younger sister Marin, two siblings who are dealing with harsh times as Fuwa is working hard to make money for a surgery Marin needs in order to treat herself. However, upon knowing that he knows one of the Zyuohgers, the Deathgalien Player Dorobozu decides to exploit Fuwa's desperate need for money in order to lay a trap for Amu and the others.

15.title: Senritsu no Sunaipâ
15.plot: The Deathgalien Player Hantajii shoots people left and right, transforming them into dolls with his sniper rifle and taking even the Zyuohgers by surprise. When only Leo and Tusk remain to face the enemy, they must find a way to outsmart the Deathgalien and save their friends.

16.title: Jûman o Sagase
16.plot: Ginis's secretary Naria appears and starts looking for Zyumans by her master's orders, assisted by the Player Mantor, and when Yamato learns that his uncle Mario was kidnapped upon being mistaken by a Zyuman as well, he comes up with a risky plan to rescue him.

17.title: Ekusutora Pureiyâ, Ran'nyû
17.plot: The Deathgalien Player Trumpas uses his cards to torment his victims and the Zyuohgers alike. Sela watches for a child who got lost from her father and manages to reunite them safely while bypassing the enemy's trick, but just when Trumpas is about to get his just desserts, the Zyuohgers are surprised with the arrival of "The World", a new and powerful enemy whose appearance and abilities are too familiar.

18.title: Kizamareta Kyôfu
18.plot: Trumpas reappears with a Blood Game even more sinister, but to stop him, the Zyuohgers must pass by The World, who easily defeated them in their last encounter, and proves himself a threat even more dangerous when he unveils his own set of Zyuoh Cubes.

19.title: Shinjiru no wa Dare
19.plot: Yamato discovers that The World is not working for the Deathgaliens out of his own will, but is under their control instead. The Zyuohgers then confront The World one more time, looking for a way to break him free.

20.title: Sekai no Ôja
20.plot: Misao Mondo was released from the Deathgaliens' control, but he regrets all he had done as The World nonetheless and declines the Zyuohgers' offer to become their ally, until Yamato's companions are captured and he asks for Misao's help to rescue them.

21.title: Purizun bureiku
21.plot: While confronting the Deathgalien Player Prisonable, Tusk and Misao end up imprisoned inside an underground dungeon. With Misao blaming himself for putting themselves in such predicament, Tusk resigns himself to look for an exit alone, until Misao decides to rise up and come to his aid, assisted by a new ally that awakens just in time to help them.

22.title: Kakusei ka? Kanchigai ka?
22.plot: When a bicycle explodes just after he touches it, Misao believes that he was afflicted with some kind of curse, until he learns that it was just a trick from another Deathgalien Player, who set up a massive bomb in the city, and the other Zyuohgers discover, much to their surprise, that Misao has a new, unexplored power that is the key to find it.

23.title: Kyojû Hantâ
23.plot: Bangray, the Megabeast Hunter, arrives on Earth looking for some new prey and gets himself involved in the Blood Game when he proves himself a powerful foe against the Zyuohgers, drawing the attention of the Deathgaliens.

24.title: Yomigaeru Kioku
24.plot: After being convinced by Ginis to join the Deathgaliens, Bangray attacks Yamato and knocks him unconscious. Once awakening, he meets his mother, who was supposed to be dead, and by the time his friends discover the true nature of Bangray's powers, they rush to help him.

25.title: Anhappî Kamera
25.plot: Worried that Yamato may be still afflicted by the events of the last battle, Misao comes across a way to cheer him up, unaware that he fell into a scheme from another Deathgalien Player. Meanwhile, Kubaru is in distress with the fact that Bangray have read his mind and attacks the hunter in order to silence him.

26.title: Taisetsu na Hi wo Mamoritai
26.plot: Yamato meets Daichi Hayashi, a friend from college and is invited to his marriage. With no leads regarding the prey he is looking for on Earth, Bangray decides to torment Yamato once more by attacking the ceremony, and the other Zyuohgers decide to fight the intruder by themselves.

27.title: Honmono wa Dotchi da?
27.plot: In another plot to make the Zyuohgers suffer, Bangray makes copies of Sela and Tusk and rigs them along the original ones with explosives, giving Yamato and the others 30 minutes to figure out the impostors and slay them before the bombs detonate, killing all four of them.

28.title: Kaettekita Uchû Kaizoku
28.plot: Captain Marvelous from the Gokaigers appear and reclaims a mysterious artifact that was hidden inside the Link Cube, but the Zyuohgers refuse to let him take a relic from Zyuland and fight him for its possession. However, Bangray appears to steal it as well, and a three-way battle begins.

29.title: Ôja no naka no Ôja
29.plot: The Zyuohgers and the Gokaigers join forces against Bangray, who summons fallen enemies of the previous Super Sentai to fight by his side. In the occasion, Yamato unlocks the powers of the Great Champion's Proof and gains a new transformation.

30.title: Densetsu no Kyojyû
30.plot: Having obtained the Whale Change Gun, the Zyuohgers begin their search for the ultimate Zyuoh Cube, Cube Whale. However, Bangray stands on their way once again, as the Megabeast Hunter intends to make Cube Whale his 100th prey.

31.title: Kyojyû Tatsu Toki
31.plot: The Zyuohgers are having a hard time trying to calm down Cube Whale, while fighting to protect it from Bangray and the Deathgaliens, but to make matters even worse, Ginis sends an upgraded version of his Gift destruction machine upon them.

32.title: Kokoro wa Ura Omote
32.plot: The Blood Games start again and the Zyuohgers come across an enemy that brings forth their hidden, darkest feelings. Misao, the only one unaffected by its power, becomes afraid of his friends' new attitude, until he decides to stop running away and confront them.

33.title: Neko Damashi No Ongaeshi
33.plot: A new Deathgalien Player challenges Leo to a Sumo fight, and when Leo finds the enemy too strong for him to beat, Amu decides to lend him a hand.

34.title: Kyojyû Hantâ no Gyakushû
34.plot: Bangray returns after recovering from the wounds suffered in his last fight, this time creating copies of the Zyuohgers themselves to fight them.

35.title: Jûôjâ Saigo no Hi
35.plot: Bangray kidnaps Yamato and demands the other Zyuohgers to hand over Cube Whale as ransom. To face their biggest crisis so far, the Zyuohgers assemble all their Zyuoh Cubes into their most powerful mecha ever.

36.title: Harowin no Ôjisama
36.plot: Halloween has come and while fighting to protect a girl called Mami from the Deathgaliens, Tusk earns her affection, to the point that she starts viewing him as her enchanted prince, much to his chagrin.

37.title: Tenkû no Ôja
37.plot: The Zyuohgers discover a giant Zyuoh Cube and while trying to activate it they are drawn into another of the Deathgaliens' Blood Games, until Bud, the Bird Man reappears, using the Champion's Proof in his possession to transform into a Zyuohger as well.

38.title: Sora Takaku, Tsubasa Mau
38.plot: Having transformed into Zyuoh Bird, Bud helps the other Zyuohgers against the Saguil Brothers, and reveals to Yamato the reason why he stole the Champion's Proof, claiming that Zyuland must be separated from the human world no matter the cost.

39.title: Karorî to Nekkuresu
39.plot:

40.title: Otoko no Bigaku
40.plot:

41.title: Saisho de Saigo no Chansu
41.plot: Deciding to personally involve himself in the Blood Game, Ginis captures Misao with the Zyuohgers confronting the alien to rescue their friend. Quval attempts to take advantage of the situation to have his revenge on Ginis, only for the Deathgalien leader to reveal his true power.

42.title: Kono Hoshi no Yukue
42.plot: The Zyuohgers take the injured Misao to the care of a doctor, who coincidentally, is Yamato's father and return to get back at Quval for kidnapping their friend. Still terrified upon seeing the true power of Ginis, Quval makes one desperate last stand against them.

43.title: Kurisumasu no Mokugekisha
43.plot: Christmas is at hand and the Zyuohgers join the festivities. When the Deathgaliens attack them, Mario witnesses their battle, and accidentally discovers Yamato's secret.

44.title: Jinrui no Ôja
44.plot: Having discovered their secret, Mario hears all the truth from Yamato and the others. Meanwhile, Bud meets Larry and the two try to analyze together the piece left from Azald.

45.title: Toketa Fûin
45.plot: While fighting the Zyuohgers, Azald reverts to his original form, and he is revealed to be the same monster that once attacked Earth and was defeated by Cetus, the original Zyuoh Whale.

46.title: Fujimi no Hakaishi
46.plot: Now back in his original form with his memories restored, Azald servers his ties to the Deathgaliens and proceeds to destroy Earth himself.

47.title: Saigo no Gêmu
47.plot: With both team leaders gone, Ginis decides to personally end the 100th Blood Game by infusing some his own cells onto the Earth, causing it to start cracking. Though Bud comes with a plan to save the planet, it would permanently severe Earth's connection to Zyuland.

48.title: Chikyû wa Waga Ya sa
48.plot: The Zyuohgers have their final battle against Ginis to save Earth from him once and for all.

imdb.plot outline: Zyuland, a world parallel to ours, is attacked by aliens, the Deathgalian. Four of its inhabitants (called Zyuman), Sera, Leo, Tusk and Amu call a young man from our world for help, Yamato. After taking human form, all five form the Doubutsu Sentai Zyuohger.
imdb.title: Doubutsu Sentai Zyuohger
plot: Zyuland, a world parallel to ours, is attacked by aliens, the Deathgalian. Four of its inhabitants (called Zyuman), Sera, Leo, Tusk and Amu call a young man from our world for help, Yamato. After taking human form, all five form the _Doubutsu Sentai Zyuohger_ (qv).
